text: In Celtic mythology, Argadnel (celtic: Maig Arggatnéul, meaning "plain of silver cloud") one of the Islands of the Earthly Paradise that were visited by Bran the Blessed.USGS Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature Feature Information Europa Argadnel Regio. Accessed 7 November 2007. In 2003, the International Astronomical Union adopted the name for a regio of Europa. ==References== Category:Celtic mythology Category:Mythological islands
title: Argadnel
